Disease,Medication
panic disorder,"SSRIs (e.g., Sertraline, Fluoxetine) | Benzodiazepines (e.g., Clonazepam, Alprazolam) | SNRIs (e.g., Venlafaxine) | Beta-blockers | Cognitive Behavioral Therapy (CBT)"
vaginitis,Metronidazole | Clindamycin | Fluconazole | Hydrocortisone cream | Probiotic supplements
problem during pregnancy,"Prenatal vitamins | Iron supplements | Antihypertensives (e.g., Labetalol) | Insulin (for gestational diabetes) | Folic acid"
acute pancreatitis,"IV fluids | Pain relievers (e.g., Morphine) | Antibiotics (if infection) | Enzyme replacement therapy | Fasting/NPO"
asthma,"Inhaled corticosteroids (e.g., Fluticasone) | Beta-agonists (e.g., Albuterol) | Leukotriene modifiers (e.g., Montelukast) | Anticholinergics (e.g., Ipratropium) | Omalizumab"
infectious gastroenteritis,"Oral rehydration salts (ORS) | Antibiotics (e.g., Ciprofloxacin, if bacterial) | Antiemetics (e.g., Ondansetron) | Probiotics | Loperamide (if appropriate)"
acute sinusitis,"Saline nasal spray | Decongestants (e.g., Pseudoephedrine) | Nasal corticosteroids | Antibiotics (if bacterial) | Acetaminophen for pain"
cornea infection,"Antibiotic eye drops (e.g., Ciprofloxacin) | Antiviral eye drops (e.g., Ganciclovir) | Antifungal drops (e.g., Natamycin) | Lubricant eye drops | Steroids (in selected cases)"
marijuana abuse,"Behavioral therapy | CBT | Motivational enhancement therapy | No FDA-approved medications | Support groups (e.g., NA)"
bursitis,"NSAIDs (e.g., Ibuprofen) | Corticosteroid injections | Ice packs | Physical therapy | Antibiotics (if septic bursitis)"
actinic keratosis,Topical 5-fluorouracil | Imiquimod cream | Diclofenac gel | Cryotherapy | Photodynamic therapy
chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (copd),"Bronchodilators (e.g., Salbutamol) | Inhaled corticosteroids | Phosphodiesterase-4 inhibitors (e.g., Roflumilast) | Oxygen therapy | Antibiotics during exacerbations"
spondylosis,"NSAIDs (e.g., Naproxen) | Muscle relaxants | Physical therapy | Epidural steroid injections | Surgery in severe cases"
injury to the arm,"Pain relievers (e.g., Acetaminophen) | Cold compress | Immobilization/splinting | Antibiotics (if open wound) | Physical therapy"
complex regional pain syndrome,Gabapentin | Amitriptyline | Physical therapy | Corticosteroids | Nerve blocks
injury to the trunk,"Pain relievers (e.g., Ibuprofen) | Ice/heat therapy | Muscle relaxants | Wound care (if external) | Physiotherapy"
vulvodynia,"Topical Lidocaine | Tricyclic antidepressants (e.g., Amitriptyline) | Gabapentin | Physical therapy | Cognitive behavioral therapy"
concussion,Rest | Acetaminophen (avoid NSAIDs early) | Cognitive rest | Hydration | Gradual return to activities
hypoglycemia,Glucose tablets | Juice or sugary snacks | Glucagon injection (emergency) | Adjust insulin or diabetes medication | Frequent meals
hiatal hernia,"Antacids | Proton Pump Inhibitors (e.g., Omeprazole) | H2 Blockers (e.g., Ranitidine) | Prokinetic agents | Surgery (in severe cases)"
allergy,"Antihistamines (e.g., Loratadine) | Decongestants (e.g., Pseudoephedrine) | Epinephrine auto-injectors | Corticosteroids | Immunotherapy (allergy shots)"
acute bronchospasm,"Short-acting beta-agonists (e.g., Albuterol) | Anticholinergics | Systemic corticosteroids | Oxygen therapy | Magnesium sulfate (in severe cases)"
degenerative disc disease,"NSAIDs | Physical therapy | Muscle relaxants | Steroid injections | Surgery (e.g., spinal fusion in advanced cases)"
pain after an operation,"Acetaminophen | Opioids (e.g., Morphine, Tramadol) | NSAIDs | Local anesthetics | Nerve blocks"
injury to the leg,Pain relievers | Compression bandages | Crutches or brace | Physical therapy | Antibiotics (if open wound)
gout,"Colchicine | NSAIDs (e.g., Indomethacin) | Allopurinol | Febuxostat | Corticosteroids"
otitis media,Amoxicillin | Cefdinir | Acetaminophen for pain | Decongestants | Tympanostomy (if recurrent)
acute kidney injury,"IV fluids | Diuretics (e.g., Furosemide) | Electrolyte management | Discontinue nephrotoxic drugs | Dialysis (if severe)"
threatened pregnancy,Progesterone supplements | Folic acid | Bed rest (limited use) | IV fluids (if dehydrated) | Close monitoring with ultrasound
gum disease,"Antibacterial mouthwash (e.g., Chlorhexidine) | Scaling and root planing | Doxycycline | Fluoride toothpaste | Surgical interventions (if severe)"
gastrointestinal hemorrhage,"IV proton pump inhibitors (e.g., Pantoprazole) | Endoscopic hemostasis | Blood transfusion | Octreotide (for variceal bleeding) | Antibiotics (e.g., Ceftriaxone) if cirrhosis present"
anxiety,"SSRIs (e.g., Escitalopram) | SNRIs (e.g., Duloxetine) | Benzodiazepines (short-term use) | Buspirone | Cognitive Behavioral Therapy (CBT)"
conjunctivitis due to allergy,"Antihistamine eye drops (e.g., Olopatadine) | Mast cell stabilizers (e.g., Ketotifen) | Artificial tears | Oral antihistamines | Cold compress"
drug reaction,"Discontinuation of offending drug | Antihistamines (e.g., Diphenhydramine) | Corticosteroids | Epinephrine (for anaphylaxis) | IV fluids and supportive care"
macular degeneration,"Anti-VEGF injections (e.g., Ranibizumab, Aflibercept) | AREDS2 vitamin supplements | Photodynamic therapy | Laser therapy (rarely) | Low vision aids"
pneumonia,"Antibiotics (e.g., Azithromycin, Ceftriaxone) | Antivirals (e.g., Oseltamivir if viral) | Expectorants | Fever reducers (e.g., Acetaminophen) | Oxygen therapy if needed"
vaginal cyst,Warm compress | Sitz bath | Antibiotics (if infected) | Surgical drainage (if large or recurrent) | Analgesics for pain
carpal tunnel syndrome,Wrist splint | NSAIDs | Corticosteroid injections | Gabapentin (if nerve pain) | Surgical decompression (if severe)
nose disorder,"Nasal decongestants (e.g., Oxymetazoline) | Antihistamines | Saline nasal spray | Intranasal corticosteroids | Antibiotics (if bacterial infection)"
dental caries,Fluoride toothpaste or gel | Dental fillings | Chlorhexidine mouth rinse | Analgesics for pain | Root canal therapy (if advanced)
