noninfectious gastroenteritis,"Antiemetics (e.g., Ondansetron) | Antispasmodics (e.g., Dicyclomine) | Probiotics | Hydration therapy | Dietary changes (BRAT diet)"
benign prostatic hyperplasia (bph),"Alpha blockers (e.g., Tamsulosin) | 5-alpha reductase inhibitors (e.g., Finasteride) | Tadalafil (for symptoms) | Surgical options (e.g., TURP) | Lifestyle changes"
spinal stenosis,"NSAIDs | Physical therapy | Epidural steroid injections | Gabapentin or Pregabalin | Surgical decompression (e.g., laminectomy)"
acute bronchitis,"Cough suppressants (e.g., Dextromethorphan) | Expectorants (e.g., Guaifenesin) | Bronchodilators (if wheezing) | NSAIDs | Antibiotics (only if bacterial suspected)"
croup,Dexamethasone (oral or IM) | Nebulized epinephrine | Humidified air | Antipyretics | Hydration
idiopathic excessive menstruation,"Tranexamic acid | NSAIDs (e.g., Mefenamic acid) | Oral contraceptives | Levonorgestrel-releasing IUD | Iron supplements"
